snippet.title: HOW TO REMOVE STICKERS ON BOTTLES | EASY NATURAL WAY
snippet.description:
LAY HO MA everyone!  One of the things I've picked up along the way is the art of removing stickers and the stubborn glue residue that it leaves behind.  Having glass jars around is great for making homemade pasta sauce, vegetable broth, making pickles, and so much more!!  Hopefully, these tips will help make your life a little easier next time you want to remove stickers from glass jars a natural way without using harsh chemicals - here are a few ways you can try:

Directions:
METHOD 1
1. Fill your glass jar with hot water.  Do this carefully.  Do not get water onto the sticker labels.
2. Wait for about 20 seconds and try peeling off the sticker labels.

METHOD 2
1. Use method 1 and remove as much of the sticker labels as you can
2. Take a kitchen towel with some olive oil and scrub against the sticker labels

METHOD 3
1. Use method 1 and 2.
2. Soak the entire jar in hot water for about 20 seconds.
3. Scrap off the sticker labels and adhesive down with a wooden or bamboo spatula, while soaking the jar in hot water in between srcubs
4. Once all (or at least most) of the glue is gone, wash the jar with some dish soap and rinse.

If you enjoyed this episode and would love to see more, remember to like, comment, and subscribe so that you won't miss a single episode!

He immigrated to Canada when he was a young boy carrying with him his ability to speak Cantonese and some broken English.  Much of his culinary aspirations stem from his background in the visual and musical art spaces.  Whether you're plant based or plant based curious, Wil believes that learning how to make food can really change your life and of those around you.
